Step 1: Calculate the Current Ratio.  
• From the balance sheet, Current Assets (End_amount) = 10,619,895.35  
• Current Liabilities (End_amount) = 624,988.48  
• Current Ratio = Current Assets / Current Liabilities = 10,619,895.35 / 624,988.48 ≈ 16.99

Step 2: Calculate the Gross Profit Margin.  
• From the income statement, Gross Profit = 2,861,769.51  
• Total Revenue = 4,879,769.51  
• Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100 = (2,861,769.51 / 4,879,769.51) × 100 ≈ 58.62%

Step 3: Calculate the Debt to Asset Ratio.  
• From the balance sheet, Total Liabilities (only current liabilities are listed) = 624,988.48  
• Total Assets = 15,528,390.30  
• Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Assets = 624,988.48 / 15,528,390.30 ≈ 0.04

Step 4: Calculate the Net Profit Margin.  
• From the income statement, Net Profit = 1,903,401.82  
• Total Revenue = 4,879,769.51  
• Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100 = (1,903,401.82 / 4,879,769.51) × 100 ≈ 38.97%

Step 5: Calculate the Cash to Current Debt Ratio.  
• From the cash flow statement, Ending Balance (Cash and Cash Equivalents) = 7,137,544.03  
• Current Liabilities = 624,988.48  
• Cash to Current Debt Ratio = Cash and Cash Equivalents / Current Liabilities = 7,137,544.03 / 624,988.48 ≈ 11.42

Step 6: Calculate Free Cash Flow (FCF).  
• FCF is computed as Cash Flow from Operating Activities plus Cash Flow from Investing Activities.  
• From the cash flow statement: Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -862,455.97 and Cash Flow from Investing Activities = -0.00  
• FCF = -862,455.97 + (-0.00) = -862,455.97

Step 7: Calculate Return on Assets (ROA).  
• ROA = (Net Profit / Total Assets) × 100  
• Total Assets = 15,528,390.30  
• ROA = (1,903,401.82 / 15,528,390.30) × 100 ≈ 12.26%

Now, presenting all the calculations in the required json format:

  "solution": {
    "Current Ratio": "16.99",
    "Gross Profit Margin": "58.62%",
    "Debt to Asset Ratio": "0.04",
    "Net Profit Margin": "38.97%",
    "Cash to Current Debt Ratio": "11.42",
    "Free Cash Flow (FCF)": "-862455.97",
    "Return on Assets (ROA)": "12.26%"
  }
}
